comments: Gives the number of ways one can write n as the sum of the numbers 2, 6, 8 and 11 if the order of the summands is irrelevant. - _Stefan Steinerberger_, Apr 09 2006In other words, number of partitions of n into parts 2, 6, 8, and 11. - _Joerg Arndt_, Jun 02 2014
